passages.text: We refresh our estimates and latest view on Mango in this report post its 2Q25 results. GS view: Maintain Sell on Mango, as we believe the company will still experience downward pressure on earnings in 2H25 given a combination of:

weaker- than- expected subscribers' growth due to a lack of blockbusters and a near term light pipeline. One of its most important titles this year in The Name of Blossom 锦绣芳华 was released on Jun 30 yet overall performance was weaker than expected with only c. \(7 - 9\% +\) viewership market share during its airing period, ranking only no. 3- 4 (vs. \(15\%\) viewership market share of Flourished Peony 国色芳华 at the beginning of 2025). Its near term pipeline is relatively light, with Whispers of Fate 水龙吟 potentially to be released by end- 2025 and other key titles are more skewed towards 2026/2027E. 2) Slower- than- expected advertising recovery amid lingering macro uncertainty, which may weigh on advertisers' willingness to spend marketing expenses, despite Mango's strong capability in producing best- in- class variety shows that attract advertisers. 3) IPTV/OTT business resumed positive growth in 1H25 yet total revenue was significantly dragged by its slashing traditional television shopping business.

Separately, Mango Excellent Media (300413. SZ) reported 1H25 results, implying 2Q25 print with revenue below (- 16% yoy, - 13% vs. GSe) and net profit miss (- 35% yoy, - 29% vs. GSe). We believe the 2Q25 results miss was primarily attributable to stagnant subscription growth, lukewarm advertising recovery, shrinking media retail revenue on traditional television shopping though IPTV/OTT back to growth, together with incremental investment in content and operating deleverage due to revenue decline.

What to do with the stock: We cut our 2025- 27E revenue estimates by - 16% - 12%, primarily on slower than expected subscription growth, weaker than expected advertising recovery together with shrinking traditional television shopping revenue. We change our 2025- 27E net income by - 15% - 7% accordingly. Maintain our coverage relative Sell on Mango Excellent Media, and revise our 12- m target price to Rmb17.3 (prior Rmb18.1) based on a lifted 18x 2026E P/E applied to 2026E EPS (vs. prior 16x 2026E P/E) considering better industry sentiment and likely enriching supply on policy tailwinds (see our previous note). -32% downside vs. average coverage upside of +5%. Key risks and what could make us more constructive: 1) stronger-than-expected content performance hence higher-than-expected net adds in 2H25E; 2) better-than-expected advertising recovery; 3) higher-than-expected revenue from IPTV/OTT and media retail; 4) better-than-expected margin dynamics.
